
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-vrancken-oauth-redelegation-01.txt'>
    <title>"Using OAuth for Recursive Delegation", Bart Vrancken, Zachary Zeltsan</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-vrancken-oauth-redelegation-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes a use case for delegating authorization by a Resource Owner to another user via a Client using the OAuth protocol. OAuth allows Clients to access server resources on behalf of another party (such as a different Client or an end-user).  This document describes the use of OAuth for delegating one Client's authorization to another Client - a scenario, which is also known as four-legged authorization.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-03-07T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
